oc:kn_40438383 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing landing pages and web copy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead with benefits, not features. Use 'you' language to speak directly to the reader. Every section should answer 'so what?' from the reader's perspective." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Benefit-driven copy creates emotional connection and clearly communicates value, which drives higher conversion rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_9c0c2468 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When adding calls to action to any content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "One primary CTA per page or email — too many choices reduce conversions. Use action verbs ('Get', 'Start', 'Download') and be specific about what happens next." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hick's Law: fewer choices lead to faster decisions and higher conversion rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_9e748f42 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing social media content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Platform-specific tone and format: LinkedIn (professional, 1,300 chars sweet spot), Twitter/X (concise, threads for depth), Instagram (visual-first, storytelling hooks), Facebook (conversational, under 80 chars for link posts)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each platform has distinct audience expectations and algorithm preferences that affect reach and engagement." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b37c3314 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning SEO for any content piece" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Identify one primary keyword and 2-3 secondary keywords per piece. Place primary keyword in headline, first paragraph, one subheading, meta description, and URL slug. Use secondary keywords naturally throughout." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Focused keyword targeting signals topic relevance to search engines while maintaining natural readability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_c748d76c a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing any content for SEO" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not keyword-stuff — write for humans first. Place primary keyword naturally in headline, first paragraph, one subheading, meta description, and URL slug." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Search engines penalize keyword stuffing; natural language performs better for both algorithms and human readers." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_db212f1b a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing blog posts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Write at an 8th-grade reading level for broad audiences; adjust up for technical audiences. Use short paragraphs (2-4 sentences), subheadings every 200-300 words, and front-load key information." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Readable, scannable content retains readers and reduces bounce rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e776e3d5 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing blog posts or email content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Blog headlines must be 60 characters or less; meta descriptions under 160 characters; email subject lines under 50 characters. These are hard SEO and deliverability limits." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Character limits ensure content displays properly in search results and email clients without truncation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

_:ref_1685bc081f7accb3 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Introduction** (100-150 words) — hook the reader with a question, statistic, bold claim, or relatable scenario. State what the post will cover. Include primary keyword." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_8f2a110f33ad748e a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Headline** — clear, benefit-driven, includes primary keyword (aim for 60 characters or less for SEO)" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_d6552e0a03a22cca a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Meta description** — under 160 characters, includes primary keyword, compels the click." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_d6d4c7d16d68410a a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Body sections** (3-5 sections) — each with a descriptive subheading (H2). Use H3 for subsections. One core idea per section with supporting evidence, examples, or data." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_e545ebb43a49aa5f a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Conclusion** (75-100 words) — summarize key takeaways, reinforce the main message, include a call to action." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

